Some new things have been discovered after the installation that are not what I have thought of or have heard anyone talk about and it would be nice to know that the Vivint staff has been told. It's not a deal breaker but it is now a bit late and I feel like it might be an unforeseen bill that could be avoided in the future for other customers. \After the install we have pigeons now on the roof every day. We have done research and found out that one pigeon can produce 25 lbs of poop in a year. Pigeons have worms in their poop and can cause damage to tile roofs like ours. We have S shaped tiles and all a pigeon needs is about three inches to make a nest. The panels are low to the tiles but now we have to get someone to put a critter guard along the panels to prevent the nesting of pigeons. We are going to be charged $15.00 a foot for the install of the guard. I called Vivint corporate and spoke with a very nice lady named Amy. She told me she would pass up my concern and I hope they come back with good news for both of us. I offered to share the cost 50/50 and I hope this is accepted.

I can send pictures if necessary.\The ground wire was installed two days ago by by Kristian Doerr who couldn’t have been more courteous and helpful.
